The figures provided by the Anec, the central trade union, speak a clear language: in the last five years, the unhindered quantities of 316 traditional cinemas have to be closed; these Zech paid most of the cinemas in large cities: 10 in Florence, 9 in Milan, Naples, Bologna and Rome, 6 in Turin and 5 in Palermo.
The most affected regions include Emilia-Romagna with 82 lost cinemas, followed by Tuscany with 44 and Lombardy with 41.
This proves that the main debtors are the multiplexkinos, because there are just these three regions in which the largest number of these modern cinemas has been registered: with 195 in the last 5 years, the Lombardy is running the lists, 81 are both in Tuscany and in Emilia-Romagna.
"The business has developed in an irrational way," says Paolo Protti, president of Anec, "it is useful that new structures also occur, but first of all, the preservation of the existing one, because it closes a hall in the city, not all of his family customers are ready to visit a multiplex cinema in the periphery instead of the old one.
