In order to obtain the sector, between 16 and 18 million euros would be needed in the year".
It is interesting to note the case of Bologna, the first Italian city, which has decided to protect it through an agreement between the community and the Anec. It is the first agreement of this kind in Italy aimed at protecting and supporting traditional cinemas, both in the historical centre and in the periphery.
The measures provided for also include tax advantages for cinema operators as well as benefits for the public in relation to proximity: it will be allowed to drive in the traffic restricted areas of the centre and also to park for more favourable parking charges.
"It is a happy initiative," said Giuseppe Tornatore, "I hope that other cities will follow our example and also develop new concepts.
But of course we also need better audio and video equipment to be able to focus on the superpower of the multiplexs, because the audience is now more demanding.
